  <text>
    <front>
      <div type="printedheader">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_5514_p1"> <seg type="com">
                        <note type="addendum" xml:id="K_5514_c0">Nachträgliche Notiz oben rechts auf Seite 1 von dritter Hand mit roter Farbe: <bibl>1105 (sammt <choice>
                                    <abbr>Beil.</abbr>
                                    <expan>Beilage</expan>
                                </choice>)</bibl>.</note>
                    </seg> <lb xml:id="p1-l1"/>
          <fw>ENGINEERING:
			<lb xml:id="p1-l2"/>AN ILLUSTRATED WEEKLY JOURNAL,
			<lb xml:id="p1-l3"/>Offices, 37, Bedford <choice>
                            <abbr>St.</abbr>
                            <expan>Street (Strasse)</expan>
                        </choice> Strand.</fw>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="dateline">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_5514_p2">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l4"/>
                    <fw>
            <placeName type="place" key="London (UK)">London</placeName>, <choice>
                            <abbr>W. C.</abbr>
                            <expan>Western Central (westlicher Stadtteil)</expan>
                        </choice> </fw>
          <lb xml:id="p1-l5"/>
          <date when="1871-10-10">10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> <fw>day of</fw> October <fw>187</fw>1</date>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="address">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_5514_p3">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l6"/>Alfred Escher <choice>
                        <abbr>Eoqre</abbr>
                        <expan>Eosquire (hochwohlgeboren)</expan>
                    </choice> </p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_5514_p4">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l7"/>Dear Sir,
			</p>
      </div>
    </front>
    <body>
            <div>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_5514_p5">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l8"/>I venture to trouble
				<lb xml:id="p1-l9"/>you with reference to the great
				<lb xml:id="p1-l10"/>work of the <placeName type="place" key="St. Gotthard (Pass)">Saint-Gothard</placeName> railway
				<lb xml:id="p1-l11"/>&amp; tunnel. We are desirous of
				<lb xml:id="p1-l12"/>publishing with as much detail
				<lb xml:id="p1-l13"/>as possible everything relating
				<lb xml:id="p1-l14"/>to this great work which now
				<lb xml:id="p1-l15"/>it would appear will be com<lb break="no" xml:id="p1-l16"/>menced, and I trust that you
				<lb xml:id="p1-l17"/>may be enabled to comply with
				<lb xml:id="p1-l18"/>my request and furnish me
				<lb xml:id="p1-l19"/>with any drawings, statistics
				<pb n="2"/>
                    <lb xml:id="p2-l1"/>and report you may have
				<lb xml:id="p2-l2"/>upon the subject. We have
				<lb xml:id="p2-l3"/>already had to thank you
				<lb xml:id="p2-l4"/>for your kind attention to this
				<lb xml:id="p2-l5"/>Journal, &amp; I trust that the pre<lb break="no" xml:id="p2-l6"/>sent request will not be too
				<lb xml:id="p2-l7"/>great a tax upon your com<lb break="no" xml:id="p2-l8"/>plaisance,
			</p>
    </div>
        </body>
    <back>
      <div type="closer">
                <p rend="center" xml:id="K_5514_p6">
                    <lb xml:id="p2-l9"/>Yours very truly
			</p> </div>
      <div type="address">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_5514_p7">
                    <lb xml:id="p2-l10"/>James Dredge</p>
      </div>
    </back>
